What we can detect:
  - NTUSER.MAN file creation in %USERPROFILE% is fully visible 
    via CrowdStrike file write telemetry (FileOpenInfo event)
  - This is the highest fidelity IOC for this technique and 
    should be alerted on immediately

What we cannot detect:
  - The actual hive manipulation via Offreg.dll has no 
    detectable API surface — CrowdStrike does not instrument 
    Offreg.dll calls
  - No registry write events fire during hive construction 
    since it operates entirely on a file rather than the 
    live registry
